			<h3 ><a href="#p1600504">Re: Investment timing strategies for 401(k) -&gt; IRA rollovers</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1600504&amp;sid=1d86bdca4ed28121979ac6dac76b1571#p1600504"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5248&amp;sid=1d86bdca4ed28121979ac6dac76b1571">retiredjg</a></strong> &raquo; Thu Jan 31, 2013 6:32 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Unless you are changing your stock to bond ratio, just sell and buy immediately - it's a sideways move.  If there is going to be time out of the market, which would allow the market to go up or down while you are on the sidelines, I might not move it all at once, but I'd invest whatever got moved immediately.</div>

			<div id="sig1600504" class="signature">Link to <a href="http://www.bogleheads.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6212" class="postlink">Asking Portfolio Questions</a></div>

		</div>

		
